          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "MPH"
                ],
                "reaction": {
                  "code": "28-NI-0(N,G)",
                  "field": {
                    "target": "28-NI-0",
                    "projectile": "N",
                    "process": "G",
                    "product": ""
                  }
                }
              },
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "A variable-energy  beam  of monoenergetic photons was",
                " obtained by Compton scattering the primary  beam  of",
                " radiative  capture  photons  from an aluminium plate",
                " with a continuously variable radius of curvature."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The target   of  Th-232  consisted  of  156.4  mg  of",
                " material (4.4 mg/cm**2)  and  was  assayed  at  100%",
                " Th-232.  The  U-236  target  consisted  of 317 mg of",
                " material (8.9 mg/cm**2)  assayed  at  89.38%  U-236,",
                " 9.20% U-235, 1.306% U-238, and 0.116% U-234."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SOLST"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Heavy-ion silicon surface barrier  detectors.",
                " Each  of  four  detectors used was positioned on the",
                " rod located  at  45  degrees  with  respect  to  the",
                " gamma-ray beam."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "PART-DET": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "FF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EXTB"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The yield points were formed from the sum of",
                " events in the four detectors.",
                "Compton scattering facility used provides a photon",
                " beam with a continuous energy distribution, rather",
                " than one discrete energy. hence, the photofission",
                " cross section could not be obtained directly, but",
                " were  extracted  from  a  measurement  of fission",
                " yield as a function of end-point energy."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "UNFLD",
                "LEAST"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The unfolding procedure was the",
                " modification of least structure method of Cook: the",
                " cook's routine was developed for use not",
                " bremsstrahlung spectrum, but the specific spectrum",
                " of Compton scattered monoenergetic photons."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "REL-REF": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "code": "N",
